==English==

===Etymology===
{{F.}} property, a little piece of paper, or a mark or title, affixed to a bag or bundle, expressing its contents, a label, ticket, {{OF.}} ''[[estiquete]]'', of German origin.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛt|-ɛt]]

===Noun===
'''etiquette'''
# The [[form]]s required by good [[breeding]], or prescribed by [[authority]], to be [[observe]]d in social or official life; observance of the proprieties of rank and occasion; conventional [[decorum]]; [[ceremonial]] code of polite society.

==== Quotations ====

*'''1885''' — [[w:Gilbert and Sullivan|Gilbert & Sullivan]], ''[[s:The_Mikado|The Mikado]]''
*:If you think we are worked by strings,
*:Like a Japanese marionette,
*:You don't understand these things:
*:It is simply Court '''etiquette'''.

